Currently it is not possible to update the repository's main branch using the API endpoint /2.0/repositories/\{workspace}/\{repo_slug} 

API documentation: [https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/repositories/%7Bworkspace%7D/%7Brepo_slug%7D#put]

Please update the API endpoint to support mainbranch update.

Currently we can't pass pipeline variables for custom pipelines to schedule jobs, so if that functionality can be added that would be great.

If that we can do by with the API only like below:-

curl -X POST -is -u UID:PWD \
 -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
 https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/repo1/slack/pipelines_config/schedules/ \
 -d ' 
 {
 "type":"pipeline_schedule",
 "uuid":"\{714a83a6-9064-495e-97ce-db28e3848a87}",
 "enabled":true,
 "target":{
 "type":"pipeline_ref_target",
 "ref_type":"branch",
 "ref_name":"test",
 "selector":{
 "type":"custom",
 "pattern":"sonar"
 },
 "variables": [
 {
 "key": "BITBUCKET_DEPLOYMENT_ENVIRONMENT",
 "value": "test"
 }
 ]
 }, 
 "cron_pattern":"15 * * * * ? *",
 "created_on":"2020-07-23T15:17:10.661Z",
 "updated_on":"2020-07-23T16:32:11.13Z"
 }'

*Summary:*
 Using the the below API to download the files from Bitbucket Cloud we see that only the readable data or a portion of the file is downloaded and not the complete file.
 This is not convenient when users need to download large files using automated APIs.

*API:* 
{code:java}
/2.0/repositories/{workspace}/{repo_slug}/downloads/{filename}{code}
(!) *Note: This endpoint returns the actual file contents and not the artifact's metadata.*

*Workaround:*
 1. Use the Downloads section of the Repository to download the individual files 
 2. Use the below link to download all the files along with meta data

*Link:* 
{code:java}
https://bitbucket.org/<username>/<repo-name>/get/master.zip{code}

When I make a call to either:
 * {{/2.0/repositories/\{workspace}/\{repo_slug}/pipelines/{pipeline_uuid}}}
 * {{/2.0/repositories/\{workspace}/\{repo_slug}/pipelines/\{pipeline_uuid}/steps/{step_uuid}}}

All of the configuration I provide in {{bitbucket-pipelines.yml}} is there, like image & script_commands. However deployment environment is also something I can specify for a pipeline step. But that detail is not returned when I call those 2 end points.

So my suggestion is either:
 * Return the value of the {{deployment}} from {{bitbucket-pipelines.yml}} is also returned
 * Return the UUID of the deployment that the pipeline step triggered, so queries to {{/2.0/repositories/\{workspace}/\{repo_slug}/deployments/\{deployment_uuid}}}
 can be made
